{
  "texts": [
    "k-mer-based association mapping with the Pt isolate BBBDB (avirulent against Lr39) 29 revealed a peak at the telomeric end of chromosome arm 2DS, corresponding to the 2.33-2.45 Mb region in the TA1675 assembly (Fig. 2c).",
    "This location overlapped with markers flanking LR39 (positions 1.20-2.84 Mb) that were identified based on bi-parental genetic mapping 30 (Fig. 2c and Extended Data Fig.",
    "The genomic region underlying the association peak contained 3 candidate genes in TA1675 (1 wheat tandem kinase (WTK) and 2 genes of unknown function), and the interval identified through bi-parental mapping harboured 16 genes (Supplementary Table 13).",
    "On the basis of functional annotations and polymorphisms compared with the susceptible Ae.",
    "tauschii accession AL8/78, the most promising candidate was AeT.TA1675.r1.2D000150, which encodes a WTK, a protein family that has a prominent role in disease resistance in wheat [31] [32] [33]."
  ]
}